{
  "texts": [
    "Preventative regulation allows for the preclusion of adverse outcomes potentially caused by AI, enabling system modifications and improvements before actual harm occurs.",
    "Early identification of potential issues also facilitates addressing fundamental technical and ethical flaws.",
    "Adopting a preventative perspective in regulatory approaches enhances trust in AI technology and ensures its safety.",
    "Ensuring transparency in AI systems is also a cardinal principle when establishing regulatory policies.",
    "Without clarity in the decision-making processes and rationale, particularly in automated subgoal-setting algorithms, it is impossible to accurately evaluate and manage associated risks."
  ]
}